Ott Nool talks about the weather for the new week.
Good evening, it will gradually get colder outside, as tomorrow a high-pressure system will dominate over the Baltic Sea, with its center over Poland.
And along the edge of the high pressure system, colder air arrives in the Baltic countries and Finland in the west wind, causing the thermometer readings to drop below zero on the upcoming night in inland areas and creating a risk of slippery roads.
Tomorrow during the day, one slightly active low pressure trough will also take advantage of the movement along the edge of this high pressure system, coming from Finland and passing over southeastern Estonia, bringing light precipitation to northern Estonia.
On Tuesday, the low pressure trough will move away to Russia and the high pressure system will cover the Baltic countries, but there will still be moisture in the area and, as is typical in autumn, the high pressure system may not always mean sunny weather.
At night, there will be variable cloudiness and occasional rain on the coast, with west-northwest winds of two to seven meters per second, gusting up to eleven meters per second on the coast.
The air temperature will range from minus two to plus three degrees, with up to five degrees on the coast.
The morning will be mostly cloudy, but there will be clearer skies in southeastern Estonia.
Rain will mainly fall on the coast and southwest and west winds will blow at three to eight meters per second, gusting up to twelve meters per second.
On the northern coast, there will also be northwest winds of seven to twelve meters per second, gusting up to sixteen meters per second.
In some places, the temperature may drop below zero in the morning, with temperatures ranging from minus one to plus five degrees, up to eight degrees on the coast.
During the day, there will be occasional light rain and the chance of precipitation will decrease in the afternoon.
Southwest and west winds will blow at five to eleven meters per second, gusting up to fifteen meters per second, and the temperature will range from five to ten degrees.
Tuesday promises to be clearer, but Wednesday will be a bit rainier.
The week will continue in a similar fashion.
The air temperature will be lower compared to the previous week, ranging from zero to four degrees at night and five to seven degrees during the day.
The days are getting shorter and the cold is slowly creeping in, have a nice evening.
